ators, are also used for optimally combining estimators. In particular, we derive optimal weights for linearly combining an estimator based on pilot bits with an estimator based on user bits. The optimal weights depend on the MSE of the two estimators being combined, and thus the accurate approximate MSE formulas can conveniently be used. The optimal weights also depend on the unknown SINR, and therefore need to be estimated in order to construct a useable combined estimator. The impact on the MSE of the combined estimator due to estimating the weights is examined. \textcopyright{} 2004 Wiley Periodicals, Inc. Naval Research Logistics 51: 720\textendash{}740, 2004. Correspondence to: D.R. Jeske (daniel.jeske@ucr.edu); A. Sampath (asampath@ti.com) \textcopyright{} 2004 Wiley Periodicals, Inc.},
